const schemaJson = `<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Service","dateModified":"2026-05-04","name":"Book Fulfillment Ukraine — Publisher 3PL with ISBN-Based Picking","description":"Specialized 3PL fulfillment for international book publishers, indie self-published authors and book retailers. ISBN-based scan picking, FEFO print-run tracking, anti-damage cardboard mailers, returns processing with photo documentation. Cross-border export to Ukrainian diaspora in Poland, Czechia, Germany, Canada, USA. Kyiv warehouse, from $0.41 per shipment.","provider":{"@type":"Organization","name":"MTP Group Fulfillment","url":"https://www.fulfillmentmtp.com.ua","telephone":"+380501444645"},"areaServed":{"@type":"Country","name":"UA"},"serviceType":"Books & Publishing Fulfillment","audience":{"@type":"BusinessAudience","name":"International book publishers entering Ukrainian and CIS markets, indie self-published authors, book retailers exporting to Ukrainian diaspora, B2B corporate book buyers"},"offers":{"@type":"Offer","priceCurrency":"USD","price":"0.41","description":"Book fulfillment Ukraine — from $0.41 per shipment (200+ orders/day). Storage from $15/m³/month. Monthly minimum $114. No hidden surcharges, NBU monthly reference rate locked into invoices."}}</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does book fulfillment cost in Ukraine vs US 3PL?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Per-order economics in Ukraine are structurally cheaper: $0.41 per shipment from MTP Group at 200+ orders/day, vs typical US 3PL pricing of $1.20-1.80 per shipment. Storage at MTP is $15 per cubic meter per month vs $35-50 in US 3PLs. The difference is rooted in Ukrainian warehouse labour cost (~$850/month for trained packer including taxes vs $4,200 in US Tier-2 metro) and Class B logistics rent in Kyiv outskirts (~€4.50/m² monthly vs $14 in US suburban park). Net savings are 60-65% on per-order cost economics with no quality compromise — same ISBN scan-based picking, same fragile-grade packaging, same returns photo documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does ISBN-based picking work at MTP for publishers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Each ISBN is bound to a specific shelf cell in our WMS at intake. Scanner-guided picker is routed to the cell, scans the ISBN barcode from the cover before pickup as accuracy verification. Re-scan at pack station before mailer enclosure provides second verification. Pick accuracy is 99.5% — fewer than 5 errors per 1,000 orders. Publisher dashboard shows real-time inventory by ISBN, movement history per copy, and turnover rates per title for forecasting reprints."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you accept small print runs from indie self-published authors?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Minimum print run accepted is 20 copies per title. We work with self-published authors printing 50-500 copies per title, typically selling through Instagram, Telegram, own Shopify store, or Yakaboo as external channel. Separate pricing tier for low-volume operations — monthly minimum is $114 (5,000 UAH equivalent). This breaks even at approximately 250 orders per month or a series of B2B pre-orders for the same title."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I ship Ukrainian books to USA, Canada, EU diaspora from your Kyiv warehouse?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, via Nova Poshta International. We prepare CN23 customs forms automatically using order data — books carry 0% import duty in most destination countries (Poland, Czechia, Germany, Canada, USA). Transit times: Poland 5-7 business days, Germany 7-10, Czechia 6-8, Canada 14-21, USA 14-25. Pricing depends on weight and country. The publisher does not need to fill out customs documentation per shipment — fully automated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you prepare the warehouse for September school season and Christmas peaks?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Ukrainian book market peaks are August-September (textbooks, school literature, children's books for Day of Knowledge) and November-December (Black Friday, holiday gifts, corporate orders). Four weeks before each peak we plan volume with each client, replenish packaging stock, schedule additional shifts. Warehouse capacity is up to 6,000 orders/day. December 2024 peak averaged 9,200 orders/day across our client base with zero downtime in fulfillment execution."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you handle book damage in transit and returns?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Standard packaging: bubble wrap around the cover, then rigid book-format cardboard mailer (B5 for standard editions, A4 for oversize). Spine sits in middle of mailer to absorb impact. Multi-book orders go in MTP-branded box or your custom-branded packaging with paper void-fill. Damage-related return rate drops from industry-typical 3-5% to roughly 0.4% in our data. Returns: photographed at intake, condition-graded on 4-point scale (A new / B open-box resaleable / C damaged buyer fault / D damaged our fault). Storage of grade-D returns is free for 14 days while you decide on disposition."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you integrate with Shopify, WooCommerce, Magento for international publishers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, natively. Prebuilt connectors deploy in 2 hours for Shopify, WooCommerce, Magento, OpenCart, PrestaShop. Ukrainian platforms also supported: Horoshop (dominant local SaaS), KeyCRM, SalesDrive, Prom.ua API, Rozetka API, Kasta. For non-standard platforms — webhook, REST API, EDI, or CSV-over-SFTP. Inventory syncs between your storefront and our WMS in real time at 800ms latency. The integration engineer on our side handles all connector work — your developers receive a webhook spec and can ignore the rest."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is war-resilient operations and zero days down since 2022 mean for international publishers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our Kyiv warehouse has operated continuously since February 2022 through every wave of strikes, with two recorded business-day pauses — both fewer than 8 hours, both during city-wide air-raid alerts, both with zero inventory loss. Three structural reasons: physical hardening (reinforced roof, ground-floor location, no glass-frontage exposure), redundant power (diesel genset with 96-hour fuel reserve plus solar backup for WMS servers), written disaster-recovery plan triggering parcel rerouting to partner warehouse in Lviv (Western Ukraine, ~530km from Kyiv) within 6 hours of major incident. Cargo insurance covers up to €3M per incident through Lloyds and a Ukrainian war-risk syndicate. SLA holds at 24-minute pick window and 48-hour dispatch in 99.5% of months including the worst three months of 2024."}}]}</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://www.fulfillmentmtp.com.ua/en/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Services","item":"https://www.fulfillmentmtp.com.ua/en/3pl-logistics/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Book Fulfillment Ukraine","item":"https://www.fulfillmentmtp.com.ua/en/fulfilment-for-books-and-publishers/"}]}</script>
